{"questionId":"25431","questionHtml":"<p>Hence state a condition in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math> that would&nbsp;imply <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> has at least one complex root.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Allow <em><strong>FT</strong> </em>on their result from part (f)(i).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark</strong></em><em><strong>]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25431","referenceCode":"22M.3.AHL.TZ2.2f.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence state a condition in terms of p and q that would imply x4+px3+qx2+rx+s=0 has at least one complex root.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"f.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Proof by induction, contradiction, counterexamples"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}